title: Two women holding banners
description: The woman holding a protest poster refering to Mubārak's view of the Egyptian people as rabbits is also holding a bunch of carrots. Phototgraphers' description: photos and video of Jan 29-Feb 11, 2011, Protests (downtown) & celebration in Maadi. Text in image:  يا نظام مبارك لا تعاملنا كالأرانب.  WE'll walk hand in hand. We shall all be (FREE) We aren't afraid. We aren't alone. The whole wide world around. WE shall over Come Some day. Translation of text in image: Mubārak regime, do not treat us like rabbits.
name: Mubārak, Muḥammad Ḥusnī, 1928-
